  "prompt": "Did any of Melania Trump's family come to her wedding? Did anyone \"give her away?\" And who paid for her wedding gown?",
  "response": "Melania Trump's wedding to Donald Trump took place on January 22, 2005, at the Episcopal Church of Bethesda-by-the-Sea in Palm Beach, Florida, followed by a reception at Mar-a-Lago. Her family, including her parents Amalija and Viktor Knavs, attended the wedding. As is customary in many weddings, Melania's father, Viktor Knavs, \"gave her away.\"\n\nRegarding her wedding gown, it was designed by John Galliano for the fashion house Christian Dior. The gown was reportedly quite expensive, estimated at around $200,000, and it is widely believed that it was paid for by Donald Trump.",
